  "introduction": {
    "subtitle": "Four axes of social tension — mapped without ideological labels. Inspired by the 8values project.",
    "description": "<p>This is not a quiz that puts you in a political box. It maps the value tensions you carry — places where two goods pull against each other. The result describes tensions, not identities.</p><p>State how much you agree with each statement. There are no right answers; both poles of every axis have a use.</p>",
    "duration": "24 statements. Approximately three to four minutes.",
    "privacyNote": "Your answers stay in this browser. The result belongs to you. Sharing is your choice.",
    "disclaimer": "Inspired by the 8values project (MIT). Items are original and not from the 8values quiz. This is not a validated political assessment.",
    "startButton": "Map my values"
  },
